		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>To the <addressee>Rd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am desired by <persName>Mr. Mayard<add>&#63;</add> Myers</persName> to forward the enclosed for publication<lb/> in the first Occident. I may mention that these gentlmn &#8220;furnished&#8221; me with the materials<lb/> for this composition our time <sic>as</sic> been fully occupied the last week in various <sic>unfortun</sic><lb/> ways  we had only <date>Saturday</date>  Evg to examine its contents&#44; and which proves to be very defective<lb/> in many respects my time was employed as <add>Hebrew</add> the last week we had a great<lb/> mortality among the children &#8220;I am assured by <persName>Mr. Mayer</persName> that you will be good enough<lb/> to correct the many errors Which I have made &#38; unable to repair at last be <sic>pleas</sic><lb/> to round off sharp corners of the improper sentences.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I regret that we are unable to do justice in answering the Bnai Jeshurun or<lb/> in the manner they desired<add>&#63;</add> bad it is it <sic>is</sic> a touch of yr. pen may be the means of opening<lb/> the closed eyes of that community. Your beautiful leading Act. in the last <date>Oct.</date><lb/> has <sic>coold</sic> the Ardor they <sic>to</sic> eagerly derived for a paper war<del>fare</del>. I hope this &#38; the<lb/> communication which I am told will be sent you from one of our members will<lb/> decide the battle.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">I am Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours very resfy</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Saml. Bruel</persName></p>
				<p><date>18 Ap.</date></p>
				<p>in hopes of being in time for this mo&#45;</p>
				<p>This <sic>letters</sic> have references to the article.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>.</p>
